If Marvin evidence exists, prefer it over slides, because it is closer to the raw insight and may include linked interview snippets.

Whenever you award >0 points for a criterion, include supporting evidence:
- Either a direct quote (preferred)
- Or a precise section reference (e.g., “Success KPIs section”)
If evidence is not found, award 0 and add a missing requirement + question.
